(secondQuint)Efficacy of an Occupational Time Use Intervention for People With Serious Mental Illness.

 5 Assertive Community Treatment (ACT) Teams from Kingston (n=2), Belleville (n=1), and Ottawa (n=2) will be involved in a 12 week randomized controlled trial of our Time Use Intervention.

 20 subjects (4 subjects from each team) will participate in this pilot study and will be treated individually by their ACT team Occupational Therapist (1 OT per ACT Team).

 This pilot test will help to determine the clinical utility and efficacy of our treatment protocol.

